%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import monotonically_increasing_id 

df_index = df.select("*").withColumn("doc_id", monotonically_increasing_id())
df_index.show()

%spark.pyspark

stop_words = nltk.corpus.stopwords.words('english')


def removeStopWords(sentences):
    # stop word removal
    stop_words = set(nltk.corpus.stopwords.words('english')) # the subset of A

    result = [word.lower() for word in sentences if word.lower() not in stop_words]
    return result


df = (df_index.rdd.map(lambda x : (x.doc_id, removeStopWords(x.Sentences_t.split(" ")))).toDF().withColumnRenamed("_1","doc_id").withColumnRenamed("_2","Sentences_t"))

import pyspark.sql.functions as F
df = df.withColumn("size", F.size(F.col("Sentences_t")))
df_filtered = df.filter(F.col("size") > 1)

df_clean = (df_filtered.rdd.map(lambda x : (x.doc_id, x.Sentences_t)).toDF().withColumnRenamed("_1","doc_id").withColumnRenamed("_2","Sentences_t"))
df_clean.show()

%spark.pyspark

from pyspark.ml.feature import Word2Vec

# Learn a mapping from words to Vectors.
word2Vec = Word2Vec(vectorSize=10, minCount=0, inputCol="Sentences_t", outputCol="result")
model = word2Vec.fit(df_clean)

# Transform each document into a feature vector
result = model.transform(df_clean)

doc_dict = {}

for row in result.collect():
    doc_id, text, vector = row
    doc_dict[doc_id] = vector.toArray()
    print("Text: [%s] => \nVector: %s\n" % (", ".join(text), str(vector)))

from numpy import array
from math import sqrt

from pyspark.mllib.linalg import DenseVector

from pyspark.mllib.clustering import KMeans

doc_vecs = sc.parallelize(doc_dict.values())

# Build the model (cluster the data)
clusters = KMeans.train(doc_vecs, 3, maxIterations=100, initializationMode="random")

# Evaluate clustering by computing Within Set Sum of Squared Errors
def error(point):
    center = clusters.centers[clusters.predict(point)]
    return sqrt(sum([x**2 for x in (point - center)]))

WSSSE = doc_vecs.map(lambda point: error(point)).reduce(lambda x, y: x + y)
print("Within Set Sum of Squared Error = " + str(WSSSE))
